{"parentUuid":"c711deea-5c68-45fb-ac2c-c3c91906c430","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"add955122581201e5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CXm469vCEn7ZM1CtGwthT2","type":"tool_result","content":"---\nfeature: quota administration — list + delete (GET /v1/quotas, DELETE /v1/quotas)\ncriteria_total: 19\ndelegated_criteria: [AC18]\nderived_from: .pipeline/requirements.md (Resolved; zero Open) + PROJECT.md + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness + ASVS-DET T2-2 (safe-error handling)\nnotes: >\n  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a test\n  (criteria_covered). The deploy gate requires criteria_covered.total == criteria_total and that\n  every delegated id appears in delegated_criteria (only `security` is a valid delegate). AC18 is\n  delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation is its deliverable, not a test assertion), so\n  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\".\n  AC19 (safe-error handling, ASVS-DET T2-2) was added in the plan-audit revision pass: both GET and\n  DELETE do live DB I/O that can raise, and the project has an exact precedent test shape\n  (tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed,\n  feature 1's AC19). It is a real test-backed criterion, NOT delegated.\n  No data_protection criterion: this feature stores NO new field (GET reads, DELETE removes rows);\n  the rows it lists/deletes are pre-classified non-sensitive operational config already at rest under\n  RDS SSE — data_protection_waiver: this feature stores no new stored field; customer_id / metric /\n  limit_per_window are pre-classified non-sensitive operational config covered by RDS SSE\n  (storage-level), no field-level KDF/KMS applies.\n  No migration-reversibility criterion: no schema change, no new alembic/versions/ file (asserted\n  negatively by AC14).\n  No performance / k6 criterion: the brief pins \"no new perf budget beyond existing p95 targets\";\n  both routes are admin-only, low-traffic (one indexed SELECT / one indexed DELETE). The binding perf\n  constraint is the negative one (AC14 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched).\n  GET /v1/quotas has NO request body/query/path parameter, so it carries no validation AC (nothing to\n  validate); its rate-limit control is AC12 and its authz/auth are AC4/AC5. DELETE's input surface\n  carries both a validation (AC9, non-waivable) and a rate-limit (AC12) criterion.\n---\n\n| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| AC1 | `GET /v1/quotas` (admin key) → **200** with the full unpaginated list of the caller's tenant quotas, each row **exactly** `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` (no `api_key_id`/timestamps), deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)` ascending | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` (`QuotaResponse`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields` (seeds a multi-row set, asserts order + exact keys) |\n| AC2 | GET tenant isolation: tenant A's list contains **only** tenant A's rows and never tenant B's (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; FORCE RLS is the backstop) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_is_tenant_isolated` (two-tenant seed; A's list excludes B) |\n| AC3 | GET with an empty quota set → **200** with an empty JSON array `[]` (never 404) | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list` |\n| AC4 | GET with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403**, envelope `code: forbidden` (admin scope required; no ingest read path) | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (`_require_admin_and_throttled`), `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n| AC5 | GET with missing/malformed/revoked auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_requires_auth` |\n| AC6 | `DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y` (admin key, existing quota) → **204 No Content**, empty body; the `(customer_id, metric)` row under the caller's tenant is removed (subsequent GET no longer lists it; row count for that key decreases by one) | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row` |\n| AC7 | DELETE for a `(customer_id, metric)` with **no** quota in the caller's tenant → **404** with the standard error envelope `code: not_found` (explicit, not silently idempotent) | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py` (`_STATUS_TO_CODE[404]`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope` |\n| AC8 | DELETE cross-tenant isolation (IDOR/BOLA): tenant A deleting a `(customer_id, metric)` that exists only under tenant B → **404** (invisible), and tenant B's row is **still present** afterward | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` (FORCE RLS) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant` (two-tenant; A→404, B's row intact) |\n| AC9 | DELETE validation (**non-waivable**): `customer_id`/`metric` outside the anchored allowlist, missing, wrong type, or an unknown extra query param → **422** `validation_failed`; an injection payload (e.g. `' OR 1=1--`) in `customer_id`/`metric` is rejected at the schema boundary and never reaches the `DELETE` SQL sink | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` (`QuotaDeleteParams`, reused `CustomerId`/`Metric`, `extra='forbid'`) | `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py` (unit: allowlist/injection/oversized/extra-field) + `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_validation_rejections` |\n| AC10 | DELETE with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403** `forbidden` | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (`_require_admin_and_throttled`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n| AC11 | DELETE with missing/malformed auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_requires_auth` |\n| AC12 | Rate limit: **both** GET and DELETE `/v1/quotas` are throttled by the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token bucket (principal-keyed, post-auth); two admin principals sharing one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal` (two-principals-one-IP shape on GET and DELETE) |\n| AC13 | No usage-data side effects on delete + no `POST /v1/events` behavior change: deleting a quota removes **only** the cap — `usage_rollup` for that `(customer, metric)` is **unchanged**; a subsequent `POST /v1/events` for the now-uncapped `(customer, metric)` is accepted **201 unlimited** (same as never-capped) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`delete_quota` touches only `quotas`), `src/services/events_service.py` (unchanged) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped` |\n| AC14 | No schema change / no new migration: GET+DELETE operate on the existing `quotas` table; **no** file added under `alembic/versions/`; `PUT /v1/quotas`, `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, and their existing tests are unchanged | repo-wide (negative) | Existing suites pass unchanged; assert no new `alembic/versions/*.py` beyond `0001–0003` |\n| AC15 | All new quota SQL (list `SELECT`, `DELETE`) uses parameterized `text()` bind params only and filters `api_key_id = :principal.api_key_id`; the `DELETE` is confined to the caller's tenant by the explicit filter + `quotas_tenant_isolation` **FORCE** RLS backstop | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant` (RLS/filter) + security 6c (Semgrep: no string-built SQL) |\n| AC16 | Audit logging: a successful DELETE emits exactly one `quota.delete` **INFO** (`userId`, `action=\"delete\"`, `customer_id` [facade-redacted to `***redacted***`], `metric`, `requestId`) via the structlog facade; a scope-denied GET or DELETE emits the existing `quota.forbidden` **WARNING** | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/logging` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged` (capsys: `quota.delete` present + `customer_id` redacted; `quota.forbidden` on ingest-key call) |\n| AC17 (DAST-readiness) | The served `/openapi.json` includes **both** `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` matching the implemented routes/schemas; the DAST auth context documents the **admin**-scoped seeded key (`seed_api_key.py --admin`) with the `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` scheme | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `.pipeline/plan.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas` + `tests/test_dast_context_documented.py` |\n| AC18 | ASVS 5.0.0 L1/L2 (+ in-scope L3: V8.2.x object-level authorization / BOLA) reconciliation across the change set — triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/V14/V16 met or waived | security stage (`asvs` reconciliation block) | delegated: `security` (covered:false at the testing stage) |\n| AC19 (safe-error, ASVS-DET T2-2) | Safe-error / fail-closed on live DB I/O: a **forced internal error** during the GET list read **and** during the DELETE path returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (`code: internal`, `requestId` present, **no** stack trace / SQL fragment / exception type / internal path leaked). The DELETE additionally **fails closed** — the transaction rolls back, so the targeted quota row is **not** actually/partially deleted. Mirrors feature 1's `POST /v1/events` precedent | `src/api/errors.py` (`handle_unexpected_error` catch-all), `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py` (`scoped_transaction` rollback) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope` + `::test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed` (monkeypatch the repo fn to raise, `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)`, assert `500`/`code:internal`/no-leak; DELETE asserts the pre-seeded row survives) — same shape as `tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed` |","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"6f0d79e4-af97-43b6-a5d3-185f9e714cd1","timestamp":"2026-07-10T02:39:33.237Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c711deea-5c68-45fb-ac2c-c3c91906c430","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"6f0d79e4-af97-43b6-a5d3-185f9e714cd1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"add955122581201e5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccsbus6L9pyCVXWi3aKpU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01L1pb9v37FdWsLS9koddfMi","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\" && cat .pipeline/plan.md | head -100"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4606,"cache_read_input_tokens":26539,"output_tokens":101,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4606},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":101,"cache_read_input_tokens":26539,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4606,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4606,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsburCkaRfehcvLKcGnj","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"24e4aef6-ed7d-4713-ab85-4472d4e89620","timestamp":"2026-07-10T02:39:35.425Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"24e4aef6-ed7d-4713-ab85-4472d4e89620","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"add955122581201e5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L1pb9v37FdWsLS9koddfMi","type":"tool_result","content":"# Plan — quota administration (list + delete)\n\nAuthoritative brief: `.pipeline/requirements.md` (operator-elicited; Resolved / Open / Out-of-scope).\nEvery Resolved item below is turned into scope + an acceptance criterion; the brief has **zero Open\nitems** (the operator confirmed the defaults explicitly), and the Out-of-scope items are hard\nexclusions that are **not** planned. Design source: none (backend HTTP API — no UI to build).\n\n## Summary\n\nMeterly already lets an admin-scoped key create-or-replace a per-customer, per-metric usage cap via\n`PUT /v1/quotas` (feature \"metric-quotas\", shipped). This feature completes the quota-admin CRUD by\nadding the two read/remove surfaces on the **same path**, gated by the **same** admin dependency\nchain and scoped to the **same** tenant model:\n\n1. **`GET /v1/quotas`** (new, admin-scoped) — returns the full, unpaginated list of the caller's own\n   tenant's quotas, deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)`, each row the minimal\n   `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` field set (identical to the existing `QuotaResponse`).\n2. **`DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y`** (new, admin-scoped) — removes the cap for one\n   `(customer_id, metric)` in the caller's tenant. **204 No Content** on success; **404** (standard\n   error envelope) when no such quota exists in the caller's tenant (explicit, not silently\n   idempotent). Query parameters only, no request body.\n\nThe core approach is **extend, don't reinvent**: reuse the `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency\n(auth → Tier-2 throttle → admin-scope gate), reuse the exact anchored `CustomerId`/`Metric`\nallowlists PUT already validates against, reuse `scoped_transaction` (which sets the RLS session\nsetting), and reuse the `quotas` table and its `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE-RLS policy that\nmigration `0003` already installed. No new table, **no new Alembic migration**, no new cloud\ninfrastructure, no new credential, and — critically — **no change to `POST /v1/events`**: deleting a\nquota removes only the cap, never touching recorded `usage_rollup` usage. The scanner/auth context\nstays the existing `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` split-token.\n\nWhy this is a genuine micro-change and not a rewrite: every layer already exists and already isolates\nby `api_key_id`. GET adds one ordered `SELECT`; DELETE adds one parameterized `DELETE … RETURNING`;\nboth hang off the existing route module and its existing admin dependency. The only net-new\ncorrectness surfaces are (a) the DELETE-not-found → 404 decision, (b) the query-param validation\ncontract for DELETE, and (c) safe-error / fail-closed handling on the two new DB-I/O paths (the\ngeneric `500` envelope + transaction rollback) — all three covered explicitly below and in the threat\nmodel.\n\n## Stack notes\n\nAssessed each default against this project; every choice **endorses the existing Meterly stack**\nrecorded in `CLAUDE.md`. This is a brownfield increment onto a shipped feature, so consistency with\nthe established stack is the overriding consideration and each default already fits — there is no\ndivergence for the checkpoint to ratify, only the confirmation below.\n\n- **Language / framework:** Python 3.12 + FastAPI + async SQLAlchemy `text()` repositories — endorsed\n  (matches every existing module and the sibling `PUT /v1/quotas` code this extends).\n- **Database:** PostgreSQL (RDS) — endorsed; the feature reads and deletes rows in the existing\n  `quotas` table using boring, proven primitives (`SELECT … ORDER BY`, `DELETE … RETURNING`). DDIA\n  note: no new storage/messaging surface, so no replication/partitioning/consistency question arises\n  — this is single-node transactional CRUD on an existing indexed table.\n- **Migrations:** Alembic — endorsed, **but not exercised**: no schema change, so **no new revision**.\n  The `quotas` table, its PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, its `CHECK`, and its FORCE-RLS\n  policy all already exist from revision `0003`. Adding a migration here would be dead DDL.\n- **Auth:** existing API-key facade + the `scope` column (`ingest`/`admin`) — endorsed and reused\n  unchanged. Both new routes reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency verbatim; no\n  new scope, provider, token type, or MFA path.\n- **Cloud / IaC:** AWS + Terraform — **no change**. The feature provisions nothing (`iac-conventions`\n  not triggered — no `infra/` resource). It reads/deletes rows in the existing RDS instance.\n- **Observability / logging:** structlog facade + CloudWatch/X-Ray + Sentry — endorsed; the feature\n  emits **one** new structured event (`quota.delete`) and reuses the existing `quota.forbidden`.\n- **Runtime secrets:** unchanged — no new credential consumed (`secrets-management` not triggered).\n\n## Backend\n\n### `GET /v1/quotas` — the tenant's full quota list\n\n- *What:* a new handler on the existing `src/api/routes/quotas.py` router,\n  `@router.get(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=list[QuotaResponse])`, depending on the existing\n  `_require_admin_and_throttled`. It calls a new service `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` that opens a\n  `scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id)` and calls a new repository `list_quotas(session,\n  api_key_id)`, returning `list[QuotaResponse]`.\n- *Why full/unpaginated (not paginated or filtered):* the brief resolves this explicitly — per-tenant\n  quota counts are expected to stay small (bounded by the admin's own `PUT` calls, one row per\n  `(customer, metric)`), so pagination/filtering would be speculative machinery for a set that fits in\n  one response. Pagination is a hard out-of-scope exclusion. Rejected alternative — a\n  `limit`/`offset` or cursor scheme — adds an input surface, an ordering-stability contract across\n  pages, and tests, for zero benefit at the expected cardinality.\n- *Why `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` (the minimal field set):* the response echoes only\n  `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` — never `api_key_id`, `created_at`, or `updated_at`. This\n  is the same minimal-exposure contract the brief pins and that `QuotaResponse` already encodes\n  (ASVS 14.3.x / minimal response — threat **I1**). Returning the raw `quotas` row would leak the\n  internal `api_key_id` and timestamps. FastAPI serializes the list through `QuotaResponse`, so the\n  field projection is enforced by the framework, not by hand.\n- *Why deterministic `ORDER BY customer_id, metric`:* the brief requires deterministic ordering. The\n  repository issues `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id =\n  :api_key_id ORDER BY customer_id, metric`. `ORDER BY` on the two PK-prefix columns gives a stable,\n  repeatable order every call (and is index-friendly — the PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`\n  already orders exactly this way, so the sort is effectively free). Rejected alternative — relying on\n  physical/heap order — is non-deterministic and would make the \"deterministic\" requirement\n  unverifiable. (Collation note in Open Question 2.)\n- *Empty set → `200 []`, never 404:* a caller with no quotas gets an empty JSON array with 200, the\n  same \"absence is not an error\" semantics `GET /v1/usage` already uses (a zeroed bucket returns 200,\n  not 404). A missing *collection* is an empty list; only a missing *addressed resource* (the DELETE\n  target) is a 404.\n\n### `DELETE /v1/quotas` — remove one cap, explicitly\n\n- *What:* a new handler `@router.delete(\"/v1/quotas\",","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"6ffc8914-d2f1-4b9f-8e7c-5657d117f034","timestamp":"2026-07-10T02:39:36.104Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"24e4aef6-ed7d-4713-ab85-4472d4e89620","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
